##  Find the equation of a tangent line at a point by finding its derivative
##  at that point
##ENDDESCRIPTION

DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros(
"PG.pl",
"PGbasicmacros.pl",
"PGchoicemacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl"
);

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a1 = random(2,4,1);
$b1 = random(2,7,1);
$c1 = random(2,7,1);
$x1 = random(-5,5,1);
$y1 = $a1*$x1*$x1 - $b1*$x1+$c1;
$m1 = 2*$a1*$x1 - $b1;

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
If \( f(x) = $a1 x^2 - $b1 x + $c1 \), find \( f'( $x1 ) \).
\{ans_rule(20) \}
$BR
EOT

$ans = $m1;
ANS(num_cmp($ans));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
Use this to find the equation of the tangent line to the parabola
 \( y = $a1 x^2 - $b1 x + $c1 \)
at the point \( ( $x1 , $y1 ) \).
The equation of this tangent line can be written in the form \( y = mx+b \)
where \( m \) is:\{ans_rule(20)  \}
$BR
EOT
$ans = $m1;
ANS(num_cmp($ans));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
and  where \( b \) is:
\{ans_rule(20)  \}
$BR
EOT
$ans = $y1 -$m1*$x1;
ANS(num_cmp($ans));

ENDDOCUMENT();        # This should be the last executable line in the problem.
